A total of R31.3 billion was spent in 2017 by South Africa’s private equity industry. This represents a 102% increase from 2016 and is well above the annual average of R14.7 billion spent over the preceding 10 years. Tanya van Lill, CEO of the Southern African Venture Capital and Private Equity Association, unpacks what’s driving funding in the private equity sector. LISTEN HERE BECOME A MEMBER   |   MEDIA & NEWS   |   DOWNLOADS +27 11 268 0041 info@savca.co.za © 2018 SAVCA. | Powered By Spheralytical